The paper discusses machine learning models that learn probability distributions from crowdsourcing scenarios. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses using Bregman divergences as an objective function, which is a technique commonly used in information theory and signal processing (cs.SI).
